COACHELLA 2023!! I’m honoured to have worked with @kumkumfernando, @metaspark and the @coachella team to produce these on-site and at home experiences bringing to life KumKum’s sculptures. It’s been an unforgettable experience building these and flying over to help set these effects up around the incredible installations. Ensuring maximum quality of the sculptures was essential, using Substance Painter I hand placed the surface patterns to allow for the ambient shadows to be baked in.

A huge thank you to everyone involved especially @itsliannebaron @tombrrrt @sophieye @lukehurd @willselviz @deeks22 and many more!

#coachella #coachella2023 #kumkumfernando #messengers #arart #areffect #grateful

Using @shapr3dapp to design a custom font to help explain the difference between XR, AR, VR, & MR. This ‘CAD for iPad’ tool allows for precise dimensions, exact edge fillet/chamfering and boolean operations to merge geometry together. Cut from my IG live last week, let me know what you think! 

XR - Extended Reality is the umbrella term for the below:
AR - Augmented Reality brings objects and experiences to the user.
VR - Virtual Reality completely immerses the user in a 3D world.
MR - Is a contextually aware typically head-mounted version of AR.

Follow for more. @csvstudio #csvstudio #XR #AR #MR #VR

Today we’re excited to spotlight another co-founder of the Metaverse Artisans @csavenables! Christian is an XR artist and developer from the UK. With a strong background in architecture and 3D design, his journey has led him to the thrilling world of XR. 

Whether working on his own projects or creating AR activations for renowned companies like the Smithsonian and Coachella, he finds unparalleled freedom in crafting in VR. 

He loves incorporating AI into his processes, not only to streamline production but also as a source of inspiration for his sculptures and artistic design iterations.

Stay tuned for more innovative works from Christian and the Metaverse Artisans as we continue to define the future of XR. #xr #vr #ar #gravitysketchcollab #gravitysketch

More world building with the help of AI #MidJourney! Using several rounds of ‘image as prompt’ techniques to ensure visual consistency and adjusting the text part of the prompt started to allow for what I call “controlled hallucinating”. Let me know what you think! All images ran through @leiainc leiapix converter to create the 3D effect with depth maps! #depthmap #aiart #texttoimage #aivideo #aiworlds

🤯Totally amazed by the power and real-time capabilities of this AI tool, we couldn’t resist jumping into VR with @gravitysketch to test it out immediately! 🌐🎨 What you’re witnessing is spontaneous innovation in action.

In a realm where dreams and daylight blend,
A lady walks where the earth and heavens mend.
She, in a gown of moon’s soft kiss,
Steps through arches of sunlit bliss.

Her silhouette, a delicate grace,
Moves in silence, a tranquil pace.
Ahead, the grand design unfolds,
A story in the golden light it holds.

A sculpture of life, of twists and turns,
In its embrace, her spirit yearns.
With every step on the wooden path,
She weaves her future, breaks from the past.

Through the structure of otherworldly might,
She journeys forth, into the light.
A dance with destiny, a fearless stance,
In the vast embrace, she joins the dance.

And on she walks, into the glow,
Where time is still, and winds don’t blow.
In halls of light, her shadow cast,
The lady ventures through the vast.

Day 03! Very fluid piece - playing with the tube tool and profiles with different materials. Let me know what you think in the comments below. I’ll be adding screen recordings of the process to my subscriber reels! #dailysculpt #onesculptaday #day03 #sculpture #nomadsculpt #fluidform #dailysculpture
Day 04! #dailysculpt #dailysculpture #sculpture #nomadsculpt #oneaday #digitalart #onesculptureperday

Day 05! Really enjoying the process and always excited to try new techniques and methods for the next piece! I took a little longer than an hour on this one (aiming for that as a minimum) this was started this morning and finished in the evening. Would love to know what people think, do you like the direction the pieces are heading in? #sculptureaday #oneaday #day05 #sculpture #nomadsculpt #sculpturechallenge #onesculptaday

Day 06 - Teal asymmetrical explorations using less colours/materials. My favourite so far 😁😆! I’d love to animate this piece and make it dynamic as the form folds onto itself. #sculpture #nomadsculpt #sculpturechallenge #onesculptaday #oneaday #sculpting #ceramic
Day 07! Nothing too serious and having more fun with materials! #sculpture #sculptureaday #sculpturechallenge #oneaday #day07 #3d #ipadpro

Day 08! This is a really easy way to name these sculptures! 😆😮‍💨 really loving the process and getting to grips with the wide range of tools available especially the Tube and Array Curve! I’m trying to push myself to do something different each sculpt either visually or new process. Excited to compare my first and last sculpt of the month! This piece also has a 3 point lighting setup which I’ll use going forward/mix up each time. Hope you’re inspired! ✌🏼 #sculpt #sculpture #sculptaday #oneaday #day08 #nomadsculpt #sculpturelovers @nomadsculpt

Day 09! Hectic day, just in time! Can’t believe sub-surface-scattering (light transmission) is possible in @nomadsculpt 🤯! #sculptityourself #sculpture #sculptaday #dailysculpt #oneaday #nomadsculpt #dailysculpture

Day 10! Not my best piece but fun nevertheless! I was going back and forth between merging the tube forms into the central structure or applying different materials to each. Another day, another sketch! Only taking an hour. #sculpture #onesculptaday #sculptureperday #nomadsculpt @nomadsculpt #fluidform #ipadpro #3dsculpting

Day 11! I feel I’m still just playing with the tools, stretching the creative muscle before planning a big piece. I think the planning is 80% of a sculpt, what to build, how to do it in the most efficient way possible then 20% actual execution. Who knows… we’ll see when the 31st comes around if that’s actually the case! 😆 How do you plan your next creative piece? #sculpture #sculptureaday #oneaday #day11 #sculptor #nomadsculpt @nomadsculpt #ipadpro #3dsculpting

Day 12! Another day another form! Going for something more solid with large carved grooves. Still aiming for 1 hour per piece. Have you tried @nomadsculpt yet? #sculpture #dailysculpt #sculptor #ipadpro #spatialart #onesculptaday #day12

Day 13! Trying something new and Mixed Reality/Virtual reality is definitely very different from “flat” Nomad sculpt! Thanks to everyone who joined, audio will be better next time! #mixedreality #quest3 #gravitysketch #mixedrealityheadset #3dsculpting #mixedrealitysculpture #mixedrealityart

Day 13! From Mixed Reality Gravity sketch into Nomad Sculpt to add materials and detailing! Very happy with this result, if you rewatch the IG livestream you’ll hear how I wasn’t very happy with this piece to begin with but with perseverance and staying positive I got a result in happy with! I hope I’ve inspired ✌🏼 #sculpture #sculptor #ipadsculpting #3dart #onesculptaday #oneaday #day13 @nomadsculpt @gravitysketch
Day 14! Not loving this one as much as the rest but done anyway! ✌🏼

Day 15! Bevelled heavy metal, something new, different, hard surface and focusing on one material and playing with roughness patterns! #sculpture #sculptor #nomadsculpt #oneaday #day15 #onesculptaday #ipadpro

Day 16 - something more organic, I really don’t like this one as there wasn’t time for secondary forms or to even finish primary forms properly. Regardless, ship it! #sculpture #sculptaday #oneaday #day16 #nomadsculpt #ipadpro #ipadsculpting

Day 17! Much happier with this piece and finally feel I’ve got more control of the tools. I also stumbled upon a really nice technique using masks to do the gold detailing! I’ve been recording my sculpt sessions and uploading them to Subscriber Reels so subscribe to get access to those and future uploads! I hope you’re inspired, all of this on an iPad! #sculpture #sculptaday #oneaday #day17 #nomadsculpt #ipadpro #ipadsculpting @nomadsculpt

Day 18! Mask mask mask! Maybe went too far with details but had tonnes of fun doing it and probably spent more than an hour…oops! No real plan for this or the the previous sculpts. #sculpture #sculptor #oneaday #day18 #onesculptaday #dailysculpt #nomadsculpt @nomadsculpt

Day 19! DRAGON 🐉🔥 Quick fun experiment in form generation maybe another day I’ll do some wings! I hope you’re inspired! #dragon #sculpture #day19 #onesculptaday #ipadsculpting #sculptor #3dsculpture #abstract #nomadsculpt @nomadsculpt

Day 20! Blending materials of different elements to make the whole piece more cohesive and trying new approaches! #sculpture #ipadsculpting #ipadpro #dailysculpt #oneaday #day20 #sculptor @nomadsculpt
